  50:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * L5                             1024 byte buffer
  51:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * U0                             1024 byte buffer; 32-bit bus
  52:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * U535, U545                     2048 byte buffer; 32-bit bus; host mode
  53:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * WB35, WB55                     1024 byte buffer
  54:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  *
  55:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * To use this driver, you must:
  56:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * - If you are using a device with crystal-less USB, set up the clock recovery system (CRS)
  57:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * - Remap pins to be D+/D- on devices that they are shared (for example: F042Fx)
  58:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  *   - This is different to the normal "alternate function" GPIO interface, needs to go through SYS
  59:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * - Enable USB clock; Perhaps use __HAL_RCC_USB_CLK_ENABLE();
  60:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * - (Optionally configure GPIO HAL to tell it the USB driver is using the USB pins)
  61:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * - call tusb_init();
  62:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  *
  63:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * Assumptions of the driver:
  64:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * - You are not using CAN (it must share the packet buffer)
  65:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * - APB clock is >= 10 MHz
  66:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * - On some boards, series resistors are required, but not on others.
  67:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * - On some boards, D+ pull up resistor (1.5kohm) is required, but not on others.
  68:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * - You don't have long-running interrupts; some USB packets must be quickly responded to.
  69:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * - You have the ST CMSIS library linked into the project. HAL is not used.
  70:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  *
  71:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * Current driver limitations (i.e., a list of features for you to add):
  72:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * - STALL handled, but not tested.
  73:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  *   - Does it work? No clue.
  74:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * - All EP BTABLE buffers are created based on max packet size of first EP opened with that addres
  75:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * - Packet buffer memory is copied in the interrupt.
  76:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  *   - This is better for performance, but means interrupts are disabled for longer
  77:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  *   - DMA may be the best choice, but it could also be pushed to the USBD task.
  78:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * - No double-buffering
  79:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * - No DMA
  80:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * - Minimal error handling
  81:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  *   - Perhaps error interrupts should be reported to the stack, or cause a device reset?
  82:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * - Assumes a single USB peripheral; I think that no hardware has multiple so this is fine.
  83:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * - Add a callback for enabling/disabling the D+ PU on devices without an internal PU.
  84:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  * - F3 models use three separate interrupts. I think we could only use the LP interrupt for
  85:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  *     everything?  However, the interrupts are configurable so the DisableInt and EnableInt
  86:SynaptiX_FDK/lib/tinyusb/src/portable/st/stm32_fsdev/dcd_stm32_fsdev.c ****  *     below functions could be adjusting the wrong interrupts (if they had been reconfigured)
